        <hl1>Life Under the Billboard Blanket; Brooklyn Kiosk Carried Sign That Turned Heads</hl1>
      </hedline>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Turning a Kiosk Into a Borough Gateway'' (April 2): The north face of the kiosk, nearest Flatbush Avenue, was -- until it was removed a couple of years ago -- the location of my all-time favorite traffic sign: ''No standing at all times.''</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Turning a Kiosk Into a Borough Gateway'' (April 2): The north face of the kiosk, nearest Flatbush Avenue, was -- until it was removed a couple of years ago -- the location of my all-time favorite traffic sign: ''No standing at all times.''</p>
        <p>I miss its grammatical incoherence and would dearly love to secure one to display.</p>
        <p>ELLIOTT SCHUMAN  Professor of Psychology  Long Island University  Downtown Brooklyn</p>
      </block>
